Barcelona’s first home fixture in the Champions League this season, will be against Inter Milan on Wednesday. The LaLiga champions drew 0-0 in their first game against Borussia Dortmund. Inter also salvaged a 1-1 draw against Slavia Prague on their home turf. Kick off is 8pm West African time. Wednesday, October 2
